1
00:00:00,833 --> 00:00:02,767
<i>You're my mother,
I'm your son.</i>

2
00:00:02,900 --> 00:00:04,867
<i> I love you, you love me.</i>

3
00:00:05,433 --> 00:00:07,233
So, how did we end up this way?

4
00:00:07,333 --> 00:00:10,633
<i> No matter what happens,</i>

5
00:00:11,567 --> 00:00:14,067
<i>the bond between a parent
and their child</i>

6
00:00:14,167 --> 00:00:17,033
<i> is formed not only by blood,</i>

7
00:00:17,167 --> 00:00:21,600
but by a kind of love you can't
<i> describe through words.</i>

8
00:00:22,833 --> 00:00:24,467
<i> I believe you.</i>

9
00:00:25,633 --> 00:00:27,233
<i> I forgive you.</i>

10
00:00:27,967 --> 00:00:29,867
<i> I love you so much, Pa.</i>

11
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:33,567
[CAROLINE SOBBING]

12
00:00:33,700 --> 00:00:36,667
<i>I know you couldn't
have done that to Mama.</i>

13
00:00:36,833 --> 00:00:38,133
<i> Attorney?</i>

14
00:00:38,267 --> 00:00:40,500
<i>There's a big development
in your mother's case.</i>

15
00:00:40,667 --> 00:00:43,167
<i>We are inviting you
to the precinct</i>

16
00:00:43,333 --> 00:00:45,333
<i>regarding the murder case
of Divine Almazan.</i>

17
00:00:49,200 --> 00:00:56,267
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

18
00:01:32,733 --> 00:01:39,633
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

19
00:01:55,733 --> 00:01:57,400
Sir, what's going on inside?

20
00:01:57,567 --> 00:01:59,033
You only summoned her
for questioning, right?

21
00:01:59,200 --> 00:02:01,867
Can't you wait for her lawyer
before you start?

22
00:02:02,700 --> 00:02:04,867
You should just wait here, sir.

23
00:02:05,500 --> 00:02:06,333
But, sir--

24
00:02:08,433 --> 00:02:10,000
[SHERWIN] Where's
Ms. Annie Al Juffali?

25
00:02:10,100 --> 00:02:11,567
We need to speak with her
immediately.

26
00:02:11,733 --> 00:02:12,900
Sir.

27
00:02:13,067 --> 00:02:14,200
Are you her lawyer?

28
00:02:14,400 --> 00:02:15,033
No, he is.

29
00:02:15,133 --> 00:02:17,400
This is Atty. Philip Sandiego.

30
00:02:17,533 --> 00:02:18,400
Andrei, right?

31
00:02:19,300 --> 00:02:21,367
I'm Sherwin,
a friend of your mom.

32
00:02:21,467 --> 00:02:22,567
Where's Miss Annie?

33
00:02:22,733 --> 00:02:23,900
She's inside.

34
00:02:24,033 --> 00:02:25,667
I don't know what's happening.

35
00:02:25,767 --> 00:02:27,733
She should've waited for us.
Let's go.

36
00:02:27,900 --> 00:02:34,933
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

37
00:02:36,867 --> 00:02:37,900
Ling?

38
00:02:42,367 --> 00:02:43,233
Ling!

39
00:02:45,100 --> 00:02:46,033
How did you know--

40
00:02:46,133 --> 00:02:48,733
Sir Toni is here, Bingo.

41
00:02:48,900 --> 00:02:49,967
He's here?

42
00:02:51,767 --> 00:02:53,100
My mother's here, too.

43
00:02:54,067 --> 00:02:55,467
She's being questioned inside.

44
00:02:58,467 --> 00:02:59,767
Ling, what's going on?

45
00:02:59,933 --> 00:03:06,967
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

46
00:03:08,333 --> 00:03:09,933
[OFFICER] Among those women,

47
00:03:10,967 --> 00:03:12,900
who are you talking about?

48
00:03:17,633 --> 00:03:19,267
The one in the middle.

49
00:03:19,433 --> 00:03:23,133
She's the one who bribed me
to declare in the report

50
00:03:23,333 --> 00:03:26,467
that suicide is the cause
of Divine Almazan's death.

51
00:03:26,633 --> 00:03:33,467
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

52
00:03:48,933 --> 00:03:50,467
- [SLAMS]
- Attorney!

53
00:03:50,633 --> 00:03:52,400
Sherwin, do something!

54
00:03:52,500 --> 00:03:55,633
Only the Tius could've
done this to me!

55
00:03:55,833 --> 00:03:56,833
[SHERWIN]
I'll take care of this.

56
00:03:57,000 --> 00:03:59,333
If Miss Annie needs anything,
call me.

57
00:03:59,467 --> 00:04:00,667
Let's go.

58
00:04:00,833 --> 00:04:02,467
Andrei...

59
00:04:02,567 --> 00:04:04,000
Son.

60
00:04:04,133 --> 00:04:06,933
This is how dirty they work.

61
00:04:07,033 --> 00:04:09,533
They're pinning all
their crimes on me!

62
00:04:09,700 --> 00:04:11,100
[ANNIE HUFFS]

63
00:04:11,200 --> 00:04:12,300
[ANNIE] Caroline!

64
00:04:13,200 --> 00:04:15,467
I already told you the truth!

65
00:04:16,400 --> 00:04:17,467
Miss Annie...

66
00:04:17,567 --> 00:04:21,333
[ANNIE] But your family
keeps feeding you lies!

67
00:04:22,367 --> 00:04:24,967
Caroline, I'm telling you,

68
00:04:25,067 --> 00:04:28,500
you won't get the justice
you're looking for

69
00:04:28,667 --> 00:04:32,133
if the culprit in your family
keeps masking their crimes.

70
00:04:32,233 --> 00:04:35,333
- [BINGO] Calm down now.
- [ANNIE] Remember that.

71
00:04:35,433 --> 00:04:38,633
- I already told you the truth!
- That's enough.

72
00:04:40,167 --> 00:04:41,567
- [HUFFS]
- Calm down.

73
00:04:42,900 --> 00:04:47,133
[ANNIE BREATHING HEAVILY]

74
00:04:47,233 --> 00:04:54,300
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

75
00:04:57,733 --> 00:04:58,700
What?

76
00:05:00,400 --> 00:05:03,500
That's what Gina told me
over the phone.

77
00:05:04,267 --> 00:05:05,767
Annie was arrested.

78
00:05:06,900 --> 00:05:08,100
[SCOFFS]

79
00:05:08,267 --> 00:05:11,233
She made this grand entrance
at the office,

80
00:05:11,367 --> 00:05:13,033
then it turns out
she's the mastermind

81
00:05:13,133 --> 00:05:14,700
behind the murder cover-up?

82
00:05:14,800 --> 00:05:17,233
The investigator is claiming
that it was her, so yes.

83
00:05:17,400 --> 00:05:19,200
She's the mastermind.

84
00:05:19,300 --> 00:05:22,400
Bettina, this is such
a huge relief for us.

85
00:05:23,267 --> 00:05:25,900
It's enough evidence to counter
the accusations against Wilson.

86
00:05:26,067 --> 00:05:27,367
But don't tell your father.

87
00:05:27,467 --> 00:05:29,100
He doesn't need any more stress.

88
00:05:29,267 --> 00:05:30,733
Especially about this case.

89
00:05:30,867 --> 00:05:32,167
Yeah, of course, Ma.

90
00:05:32,267 --> 00:05:34,533
But I'll let Irene know.

91
00:05:34,667 --> 00:05:35,567
I mean...

92
00:05:35,667 --> 00:05:37,967
I know that this is
another huge mess.

93
00:05:38,133 --> 00:05:40,233
- But she deserves to know.
- Yeah.

94
00:05:40,333 --> 00:05:42,533
I hope that Annie rots in jail.

95
00:05:42,933 --> 00:05:44,200
Is it her?

96
00:05:45,233 --> 00:05:47,433
Is Annie the woman
you saw that night?

97
00:05:49,067 --> 00:05:50,267
[SIGHS DEEPLY]

98
00:05:50,800 --> 00:05:52,133
She fits the description.

99
00:05:52,733 --> 00:05:53,600
Long hair.

100
00:05:54,167 --> 00:05:55,767
It could be her. I'm not sure.

101
00:05:58,500 --> 00:06:01,633
That's not how you're
going to answer in court.

102
00:06:02,400 --> 00:06:05,067
All you're going
to say is, "Yes.

103
00:06:05,767 --> 00:06:07,300
She's the one I saw."

104
00:06:08,833 --> 00:06:10,333
Won't I get sued for that?

105
00:06:10,867 --> 00:06:12,767
I'm not really sure it's her.

106
00:06:13,433 --> 00:06:16,733
Only you and Divine know
what happened that time.

107
00:06:17,667 --> 00:06:20,233
The court's not going to ask
a dead person, right?

108
00:06:20,800 --> 00:06:23,733
So it's going to be your
statement versus Annie's.

109
00:06:24,967 --> 00:06:27,100
So, I will ask you again,

110
00:06:28,167 --> 00:06:32,400
is Annie the one you saw
the night Divine died?

111
00:06:33,300 --> 00:06:35,467
Yes. Annie is the one I saw.

112
00:06:37,100 --> 00:06:38,800
Keep that narrative.

113
00:06:39,667 --> 00:06:41,467
I'll handle the court.

114
00:06:41,867 --> 00:06:46,533
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

115
00:06:57,667 --> 00:06:58,633
[BINGO] Ling.

116
00:06:59,700 --> 00:07:00,600
Li...

117
00:07:01,500 --> 00:07:02,433
Ling!

118
00:07:03,033 --> 00:07:04,300
Hold on.

119
00:07:06,067 --> 00:07:08,100
We shouldn't talk
for now, Bingo.

120
00:07:08,833 --> 00:07:11,200
Ling, we have a problem.

121
00:07:11,333 --> 00:07:12,800
We should talk about it.

122
00:07:12,900 --> 00:07:14,267
Not now.

123
00:07:15,367 --> 00:07:18,167
I don't want to say anything
I might regret.

124
00:07:23,867 --> 00:07:28,700
[SULLEN MUSIC PLAYING]

125
00:07:31,333 --> 00:07:32,667
[VAN DOOR CLOSES]

126
00:07:33,567 --> 00:07:35,833
[VAN LEAVING]

127
00:07:43,833 --> 00:07:44,833
[SNOOP] Right here, sir.

128
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:47,133
My payment.

129
00:07:47,767 --> 00:07:48,700
Oops.

130
00:07:50,100 --> 00:07:51,200
Boy!

131
00:07:51,700 --> 00:07:53,567
Sir, can you hand me
my slipper?

132
00:07:54,067 --> 00:07:55,567
Thank you.

133
00:07:56,067 --> 00:07:57,200
Boy, thanks for coming.

134
00:07:57,300 --> 00:07:58,700
Oh, come on, boy.

135
00:07:58,867 --> 00:08:01,667
If I had wings, I would've
been here sooner.

136
00:08:01,767 --> 00:08:03,000
So, where's your mom?

137
00:08:03,633 --> 00:08:06,267
The lawyer is still preparing
her defense.

138
00:08:06,933 --> 00:08:09,700
If it's murder,
they'll lock her up, right?

139
00:08:10,767 --> 00:08:12,833
I'll wait for what
the lawyer will say.

140
00:08:13,567 --> 00:08:15,367
Got it. So, what do you need?

141
00:08:15,467 --> 00:08:17,833
Have you eaten?
I got some food here.

142
00:08:18,700 --> 00:08:21,100
You need transport?
I can call Koriks.

143
00:08:21,267 --> 00:08:23,267
It's Grandma and Papi.

144
00:08:23,967 --> 00:08:25,567
Can you take care of them?

145
00:08:25,667 --> 00:08:28,267
Of course. You don't have
to tell me twice.

146
00:08:28,433 --> 00:08:29,767
Thank you, boy.

147
00:08:30,667 --> 00:08:33,633
With all that's happening,
I'm not sure when I'd get home.

148
00:08:33,767 --> 00:08:36,300
[SULLEN MUSIC PLAYING]

149
00:08:36,433 --> 00:08:37,567
[CLICKS TONGUE]

150
00:08:38,767 --> 00:08:40,367
[TAPPING BACK]

151
00:08:41,067 --> 00:08:42,267
What do you got?

152
00:08:43,600 --> 00:08:45,233
Crispy pork belly
and sizzling pork bits.

153
00:08:45,333 --> 00:08:46,800
- Oh, yeah?
- Yeah.

154
00:08:47,267 --> 00:08:48,733
Still fresh and warm.

155
00:08:49,467 --> 00:08:51,433
I'm worried about Bingo.

156
00:08:52,833 --> 00:08:57,267
When Papa was a suspect,
I took it really hard.

157
00:08:58,300 --> 00:09:00,767
And now that Miss Annie
is being accused,

158
00:09:01,467 --> 00:09:03,633
I think he's feeling the same.

159
00:09:05,133 --> 00:09:07,333
Do you believe his mom
is responsible

160
00:09:07,467 --> 00:09:09,500
for your mom's death?

161
00:09:16,967 --> 00:09:19,567
I think you need to talk
to Bingo, Caroline.

162
00:09:22,333 --> 00:09:23,733
[JERSEY] Stephen, wait.

163
00:09:24,633 --> 00:09:27,800
Are you sure you'd be fine
hearing all of this?

164
00:09:28,300 --> 00:09:29,467
As I said before,

165
00:09:29,567 --> 00:09:31,967
I'm going to give whatever
support Caroline needs.

166
00:09:32,133 --> 00:09:35,033
This isn't easy for her.
She's involved in both parties.

167
00:09:35,967 --> 00:09:39,100
Both her family
and her friend's family.

168
00:09:39,200 --> 00:09:43,300
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

169
00:09:43,400 --> 00:09:45,467
Caroline, if you really
are friends,

170
00:09:45,633 --> 00:09:47,500
you'll find a way to get
through this together

171
00:09:47,667 --> 00:09:49,533
without ruining
your friendship.

172
00:09:52,500 --> 00:09:54,467
Hmm... Stephen.

173
00:09:56,467 --> 00:09:58,167
You can do this, Caroline.

174
00:09:58,333 --> 00:10:00,267
And whatever happens,
me and Jersey are here.

175
00:10:00,367 --> 00:10:01,600
- Right?
- Yup.

176
00:10:02,200 --> 00:10:04,133
We're here for you, okay?

177
00:10:04,233 --> 00:10:05,233
Thank you.

178
00:10:05,667 --> 00:10:07,000
Thank you, Stephen.

179
00:10:10,533 --> 00:10:14,633
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

180
00:10:42,133 --> 00:10:43,033
Ma.

181
00:10:47,233 --> 00:10:50,533
Bingo, you should go home.

182
00:10:51,733 --> 00:10:53,900
I'll stay here until tonight.

183
00:10:54,067 --> 00:10:56,267
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

184
00:10:56,400 --> 00:10:57,667
[SIGHS]

185
00:11:00,200 --> 00:11:01,367
Bingo...

186
00:11:02,967 --> 00:11:05,700
I'm not perfect.

187
00:11:07,900 --> 00:11:10,567
I've made many mistakes
in my life.

188
00:11:13,333 --> 00:11:17,400
But I didn't kill Divine.

189
00:11:19,400 --> 00:11:23,567
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

190
00:11:34,333 --> 00:11:36,433
I believe you, Ma.

191
00:11:42,800 --> 00:11:44,100
[SIGHS]

192
00:11:48,167 --> 00:11:50,733
That's all that matters to me.

193
00:11:52,267 --> 00:11:56,767
I don't care what others think.

194
00:11:57,700 --> 00:12:00,467
As long as you believe me...

195
00:12:02,500 --> 00:12:04,100
it's enough for me.

196
00:12:10,533 --> 00:12:12,433
[SNIFFLES, SIGHS]

197
00:12:16,567 --> 00:12:19,033
[GRIM MUSIC PLAYING]

198
00:12:19,167 --> 00:12:21,000
I don't remember
this picture.

199
00:12:21,467 --> 00:12:23,767
It was found at the crime scene.

200
00:12:23,867 --> 00:12:26,933
I looked for it
so I can show it to you.

201
00:12:27,833 --> 00:12:29,667
I remember the woman's face.

202
00:12:31,000 --> 00:12:35,467
She was the one who paid me
to make it seem like a suicide.

203
00:12:36,533 --> 00:12:37,833
According to the report,

204
00:12:38,000 --> 00:12:40,500
both their DNA's were found
in that picture.

205
00:12:41,333 --> 00:12:45,667
Didn't you say she admitted that
she was there that night?

206
00:12:46,667 --> 00:12:48,633
Don't you think
that's motive, Caroline?

207
00:12:51,367 --> 00:12:53,700
She said she was hit
by a car.

208
00:12:54,767 --> 00:12:57,200
She was hunted down
because of what she saw.

209
00:12:58,900 --> 00:13:01,400
How sure are you
that it wasn't an accident

210
00:13:01,533 --> 00:13:03,700
and someone was really
trying to kill her?

211
00:13:03,867 --> 00:13:08,200
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

212
00:13:19,600 --> 00:13:20,567
[ATTORNEY] He's here.

213
00:13:33,133 --> 00:13:34,833
- Mr. Tiu.
- Yes, sir?

214
00:13:35,633 --> 00:13:38,733
Can you tell us
what happened that night?

215
00:13:41,933 --> 00:13:43,833
I saw a woman covered in blood

216
00:13:44,633 --> 00:13:47,067
running out
of Auntie Divine's house.

217
00:13:48,367 --> 00:13:52,733
If you did see it,
why are you just telling us now?

218
00:13:53,400 --> 00:13:55,067
I wasn't sure back then.

219
00:13:55,633 --> 00:13:56,767
I was still young.

220
00:13:57,500 --> 00:13:59,300
But now,
there's no turning back.

221
00:13:59,467 --> 00:14:01,767
I need to tell the truth
of what happened that night.

222
00:14:02,333 --> 00:14:04,433
[OFFICER]
And what is the truth, Mr. Tiu?

223
00:14:05,267 --> 00:14:07,233
I saw Annie Mariano that night.

224
00:14:07,333 --> 00:14:12,700
[GRIM MUSIC PLAYING]

225
00:14:30,600 --> 00:14:33,167
What is it?
You haven't said a word.

226
00:14:34,367 --> 00:14:36,300
You told me before

227
00:14:37,433 --> 00:14:39,900
that you kept quiet
because you weren't sure

228
00:14:40,000 --> 00:14:41,633
about the woman's identity.

229
00:14:43,500 --> 00:14:47,133
But why do you sound
so sure back at the precinct?

230
00:14:48,267 --> 00:14:50,967
I wasn't sure before
because it had been so long.

231
00:14:51,133 --> 00:14:54,567
But when I saw Annie Mariano's
face, it all came back to me.

232
00:14:55,033 --> 00:14:56,733
It was her face I saw.

233
00:14:57,167 --> 00:14:59,733
So, yes, I'm sure it was her.

234
00:14:59,833 --> 00:15:05,133
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

235
00:15:12,500 --> 00:15:15,333
<i>It was an act of courage
done by Charleston Tiu,</i>

236
00:15:15,467 --> 00:15:18,867
<i>eldest son of business tycoon
Wilson Tiu</i>

237
00:15:19,033 --> 00:15:21,333
<i>of the Golden Lotus
Corporation.</i>

238
00:15:21,467 --> 00:15:24,533
<i>in the middle of the
murder investigation</i>

239
00:15:24,700 --> 00:15:29,633
<i>of the woman once linked
to his father 13 years ago.</i>

240
00:15:30,833 --> 00:15:34,800
<i>He showed up as a witness
against Annie Al Juffali,</i>

241
00:15:34,900 --> 00:15:39,000
<i>who's now the
major shareholder of GLC.</i>

242
00:15:39,200 --> 00:15:41,167
<i> Her connection to the GLC</i>

243
00:15:41,267 --> 00:15:44,533
<i>has brought even more
interest in the case.</i>

244
00:15:44,667 --> 00:15:47,033
[REPORTERS SPEAKING
INDISTINCTLY]

245
00:15:47,167 --> 00:15:48,300
[REMOTE BEEPS]

246
00:15:50,567 --> 00:15:53,133
Good. We don't need
to hear that kind of news.

247
00:15:53,233 --> 00:15:54,700
We know the truth, right?

248
00:15:55,267 --> 00:15:56,833
And it will come out.

249
00:15:58,833 --> 00:15:59,833
Let's eat.

250
00:16:00,767 --> 00:16:01,667
Yes.

251
00:16:01,767 --> 00:16:05,667
Time is the ultimate
truth-teller.

252
00:16:07,333 --> 00:16:09,200
I think I've heard that before.

253
00:16:09,700 --> 00:16:10,733
Well, it's true.

254
00:16:11,300 --> 00:16:12,400
Sheesh...

255
00:16:13,267 --> 00:16:15,400
I'm praying for good news.

256
00:16:15,533 --> 00:16:16,900
Please give us some good news.

257
00:16:17,067 --> 00:16:18,200
[NENE] Please.

258
00:16:18,300 --> 00:16:21,067
[MONCHING] Oh, dear. [SIGHS]

259
00:16:21,200 --> 00:16:22,733
I have to go somewhere.

260
00:16:23,600 --> 00:16:25,533
- [MONCHING] Huh?
- [NENE] Where are you going?

261
00:16:26,767 --> 00:16:27,867
What's that about?

262
00:16:29,367 --> 00:16:34,233
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

263
00:16:40,267 --> 00:16:42,533
[VEHICLE APPROACHING]

264
00:16:47,333 --> 00:16:48,967
Ling! Ling!

265
00:16:50,067 --> 00:16:51,100
You can go on ahead.

266
00:16:51,233 --> 00:16:52,767
Ling, we have to talk.

267
00:16:53,400 --> 00:16:55,200
- Please.
- What are you doing here?

268
00:16:55,300 --> 00:16:57,533
We have to talk.

269
00:16:57,633 --> 00:16:58,400
Not now.

270
00:16:58,500 --> 00:17:01,567
Ling, come on, I'm begging you.

271
00:17:05,167 --> 00:17:06,233
Please.

272
00:17:06,333 --> 00:17:07,800
Let's do it inside.

273
00:17:14,133 --> 00:17:16,867
Another day, another problem.

274
00:17:17,000 --> 00:17:18,167
No fail.

275
00:17:18,333 --> 00:17:19,933
Gosh, this family.

276
00:17:20,967 --> 00:17:22,933
I know them well enough,

277
00:17:23,033 --> 00:17:25,767
but I'm still shocked about
what's been going on.

278
00:17:26,633 --> 00:17:29,167
First it was Carlo,
and then Charleston,

279
00:17:29,333 --> 00:17:31,767
and then Papa, and now
it's Annie Al Juffali.

280
00:17:31,867 --> 00:17:35,767
I haven't asked Bingo this yet,
but it really baffles me.

281
00:17:36,433 --> 00:17:38,667
How could it be his mother?

282
00:17:38,833 --> 00:17:40,100
I don't know.

283
00:17:40,833 --> 00:17:44,300
But Charleston testified
that he was Annie that night.

284
00:17:44,933 --> 00:17:45,933
But...

285
00:17:46,300 --> 00:17:48,067
But something's bothering me.

286
00:17:48,200 --> 00:17:50,300
Something's not connecting.

287
00:17:51,200 --> 00:17:52,367
[SIGHS]

288
00:17:56,867 --> 00:17:57,800
Hey.

289
00:17:59,367 --> 00:18:01,000
Does it bother you?

290
00:18:03,667 --> 00:18:05,933
It's just so embarrassing.

291
00:18:06,033 --> 00:18:07,500
This is my world.

292
00:18:08,400 --> 00:18:10,667
Welcome to the world
of the Tius,

293
00:18:11,467 --> 00:18:14,300
where nothing is nice
and everything's spice.

294
00:18:14,400 --> 00:18:17,000
They'll do everything,
even shady dealings,

295
00:18:17,167 --> 00:18:19,300
just to protect their own stake.

296
00:18:22,067 --> 00:18:22,867
Come on.

297
00:18:24,200 --> 00:18:25,533
It's okay.

298
00:18:27,867 --> 00:18:30,700
Sometimes, people are forced
to do the wrong thing.

299
00:18:32,367 --> 00:18:34,700
Especially if it concerns
their family.

300
00:18:35,900 --> 00:18:37,867
If it means protecting
their family.

301
00:18:38,033 --> 00:18:42,500
[SULLEN MUSIC PLAYING]

302
00:18:46,433 --> 00:18:47,533
[GLASS CLATTERS]

303
00:18:48,067 --> 00:18:49,533
Irene, I'm sorry.

304
00:18:49,833 --> 00:18:50,900
[SCOFFS]

305
00:18:51,900 --> 00:18:53,667
Why are you saying sorry?
I'm the one--

306
00:18:53,767 --> 00:18:55,700
I've done something
to your family...

307
00:18:57,233 --> 00:18:58,733
for the sake of my family.

308
00:19:07,867 --> 00:19:08,733
What?

309
00:19:08,867 --> 00:19:10,567
My mother would never do that.

310
00:19:11,033 --> 00:19:12,933
She did something
for money before,

311
00:19:13,067 --> 00:19:14,667
but she's not a murderer.

312
00:19:15,567 --> 00:19:17,433
And you believe that?

313
00:19:19,933 --> 00:19:22,167
I thought you were angry
at your mom.

314
00:19:22,300 --> 00:19:24,400
You hated her, right?

315
00:19:24,533 --> 00:19:25,867
And now look at you.

316
00:19:26,367 --> 00:19:28,667
Coming here just to defend her.

317
00:19:29,667 --> 00:19:30,933
What changed?

318
00:19:31,067 --> 00:19:31,967
Ling...

319
00:19:32,100 --> 00:19:34,200
Is it because you now
have the GLC?

320
00:19:35,000 --> 00:19:35,800
What?

321
00:19:35,933 --> 00:19:37,767
Isn't that what you've
dreamed of?

322
00:19:38,800 --> 00:19:41,300
- To be like us?
- Hey, wait a minute.

323
00:19:41,433 --> 00:19:42,467
Slow down.

324
00:19:42,600 --> 00:19:44,300
Watch what you're saying.

325
00:19:44,433 --> 00:19:45,967
Am I wrong?

326
00:19:46,100 --> 00:19:47,367
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

327
00:19:47,500 --> 00:19:50,467
All evidence points
to your mom.

328
00:19:50,600 --> 00:19:52,467
She killed my mother.

329
00:19:53,300 --> 00:19:54,800
What makes you so sure?

330
00:19:56,400 --> 00:19:58,700
Were you there? Did you see it?

331
00:19:59,600 --> 00:20:01,867
The investigation isn't over yet
and you're already judging her.

332
00:20:02,033 --> 00:20:02,900
What about you?

333
00:20:03,600 --> 00:20:05,233
Were you there?

334
00:20:05,333 --> 00:20:06,833
Are you sure it wasn't her?

335
00:20:07,600 --> 00:20:10,300
Bingo, you don't know your mom.

336
00:20:10,433 --> 00:20:11,933
You don't know her either.

337
00:20:12,100 --> 00:20:14,333
He left you because
she went into hiding.

338
00:20:14,467 --> 00:20:16,433
Because someone wants
to kill her.

339
00:20:16,600 --> 00:20:18,667
She married a rich man, Bingo.

340
00:20:18,800 --> 00:20:20,300
- And now--
- What?

341
00:20:20,433 --> 00:20:21,800
And now what?

342
00:20:23,033 --> 00:20:25,600
Why would she seek revenge
if she's the actual killer?

343
00:20:26,267 --> 00:20:27,900
And what about your father?

344
00:20:28,600 --> 00:20:30,567
How come you don't
suspect him anymore?

345
00:20:31,667 --> 00:20:33,500
Think about it, Ling.

346
00:20:34,433 --> 00:20:36,567
We're both victims
of your family.

347
00:20:36,700 --> 00:20:38,267
Don't you realize that?

348
00:20:40,867 --> 00:20:44,933
You have no right to talk
about my family that way.

349
00:20:46,133 --> 00:20:49,167
And you have no right to talk
about my mother that way.

350
00:20:57,533 --> 00:21:01,967
[GRIM MUSIC CONTINUES]

351
00:21:03,333 --> 00:21:04,267
[CARLO SIGHS]

352
00:21:05,867 --> 00:21:07,700
I saw you on the news today

353
00:21:08,833 --> 00:21:11,633
testifying against
Annie Al Juffali.

354
00:21:13,433 --> 00:21:15,133
Are you sure it was her?

355
00:21:17,167 --> 00:21:20,333
It's the only way to get even
after what she did to the GLC.

356
00:21:23,233 --> 00:21:24,700
It's not enough.

357
00:21:26,533 --> 00:21:28,633
Papa gave his life
to the company.

358
00:21:29,733 --> 00:21:32,833
That Annie planned everything
from the start.

359
00:21:33,933 --> 00:21:36,200
I'm sure she still has
a lot of secrets.

360
00:21:45,033 --> 00:21:46,200
[SIGHS]

361
00:21:50,567 --> 00:21:52,067
[SIGHS]

362
00:21:59,533 --> 00:22:01,100
You told me before...

363
00:22:02,233 --> 00:22:06,733
["YOU'LL BE SAFE HERE"
INSTRUMENTAL PLAYING]

364
00:22:07,533 --> 00:22:09,433
...no matter how many times
lightning strikes...

365
00:22:16,567 --> 00:22:18,200
You also told me...

366
00:22:19,667 --> 00:22:22,033
that you'd be there
for me more times

367
00:22:22,133 --> 00:22:25,200
than there are stars in the sky.

368
00:22:33,267 --> 00:22:35,933
- I'm sorry for what I said.
- Sorry.

369
00:22:41,300 --> 00:22:42,367
Sorry, Bingo.

370
00:22:44,333 --> 00:22:49,900
["YOU'LL BE SAFE HERE"
INSTRUMENTAL CONTINUES]

371
00:23:10,833 --> 00:23:14,067
Are we going to let this
destroy us?

372
00:23:18,000 --> 00:23:20,967
Let's just allow the authorities
to handle this.

373
00:23:22,067 --> 00:23:24,800
From now on,
let's not talk about it.

374
00:23:25,633 --> 00:23:26,500
Okay?

375
00:23:30,800 --> 00:23:32,167
We'll get through this.

376
00:23:40,900 --> 00:23:42,767
What the hell
are you doing here?

377
00:23:43,533 --> 00:23:45,833
Guard, throw him out!
Caroline, get inside.

378
00:23:45,967 --> 00:23:48,133
- Hold on.
- Get inside!

379
00:23:48,633 --> 00:23:49,633
Wait...

380
00:23:49,733 --> 00:23:51,667
Stay away from us,
you son of a murderer.

381
00:23:51,800 --> 00:23:52,800
Bettina!

382
00:23:53,300 --> 00:23:55,200
Everything that's been
happening to us

383
00:23:55,400 --> 00:23:57,033
is because of them.

384
00:23:57,200 --> 00:23:59,833
So from now on, you're not
allowed to talk to him.

385
00:23:59,933 --> 00:24:01,400
We're not doing anything wrong.

386
00:24:01,567 --> 00:24:02,567
[BETTINA] Oh, really?

387
00:24:03,833 --> 00:24:06,867
You may have tricked my sister,
but I'm not like her.

388
00:24:07,000 --> 00:24:09,000
Get out! Throw him out of here!

389
00:24:09,100 --> 00:24:10,833
- Let me go. Ling--
- Caroline, let's go.

390
00:24:10,933 --> 00:24:12,867
Make sure he never comes back.

391
00:24:14,533 --> 00:24:15,967
Let me go!

392
00:24:16,600 --> 00:24:18,333
You're so stubborn.

393
00:24:18,500 --> 00:24:19,367
Bettina!

394
00:24:20,533 --> 00:24:22,000
- Stay there.
- [GROANS]

395
00:24:22,733 --> 00:24:25,333
You have no right
to treat Bingo that way.

396
00:24:26,067 --> 00:24:27,033
Wow!

397
00:24:27,667 --> 00:24:29,500
How do you live with yourself?

398
00:24:30,367 --> 00:24:32,033
When you were accusing
this family,

399
00:24:32,200 --> 00:24:33,733
you were furious at us.

400
00:24:34,100 --> 00:24:36,200
No one was safe from your wrath.

401
00:24:36,300 --> 00:24:38,433
But now, all the answers
to your questions

402
00:24:38,567 --> 00:24:40,033
are waving right
in front of you,

403
00:24:40,133 --> 00:24:41,867
and you'll still let Bingo
off the hook.

404
00:24:41,967 --> 00:24:43,733
Her mom is still under
investigation.

405
00:24:43,900 --> 00:24:45,500
So you don't believe
she's guilty?

406
00:24:46,100 --> 00:24:48,033
You'd rather believe
Bingo's story.

407
00:24:48,200 --> 00:24:50,900
Because he'll never lie to me.
That's why I gave him a chance.

408
00:24:51,067 --> 00:24:53,100
Oh my god, Caroline!

409
00:24:53,900 --> 00:24:55,867
Are you really that stupid?!

410
00:24:57,900 --> 00:25:00,100
This conversation is pointless.

411
00:25:00,233 --> 00:25:01,900
Why?

412
00:25:02,433 --> 00:25:03,867
Because I'm right?

413
00:25:04,600 --> 00:25:06,233
That guy is the son

414
00:25:06,400 --> 00:25:08,967
of the woman
that killed your mother!

415
00:25:10,167 --> 00:25:12,100
And you're still defending him.

416
00:25:12,667 --> 00:25:14,867
Tell me, Caroline, why?

417
00:25:14,967 --> 00:25:16,267
Tell me why!

418
00:25:16,433 --> 00:25:17,900
Because I love him!

419
00:25:20,100 --> 00:25:25,233
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

420
00:25:26,633 --> 00:25:29,867
<i> This will be last time
</i>you say bad things about Bingo,

421
00:25:29,967 --> 00:25:32,400
<i> or I will be your enemy.</i>

422
00:25:32,500 --> 00:25:34,767
<i>Are you seriously
taking her side now?</i>

423
00:25:34,933 --> 00:25:36,633
<i>I think you're forgetting
that Caroline</i>

424
00:25:36,800 --> 00:25:39,400
<i>is the root of all misfortunes
happening in this family.</i>

425
00:25:39,500 --> 00:25:43,000
<i>Please accept everything
I'm going to give to my son.</i>

426
00:25:43,133 --> 00:25:45,100
<i>It's likely she's connected
to the hacking.</i>

427
00:25:45,267 --> 00:25:46,767
<i>And then kidnapping
Caroline and Irene?</i>

428
00:25:46,867 --> 00:25:47,833
<i> That's her, too.</i>

429
00:25:47,967 --> 00:25:49,433
<i>Her strategy
is so damn effective.</i>

430
00:25:49,533 --> 00:25:52,433
<i>Sherwin, you have to give
everything to Andrei,</i>

431
00:25:52,533 --> 00:25:57,000
<i>including my house,
all of my properties, and GLC.</i>
